Frequently asked questions
Why is Outlook changing my URLs style?
 Links change style when copying from a template to Outlook. Microsoft recently changed the
way some links/smartlinks work. The only workaround for this issue is to create your links in
Outlook in the desired style.
Learn more
Can I use MetricHPE font?
 No, Arial should be used for email text. MetricHPE should not be used for body copy, since
email recipients can only see MetricHPE text if they have the font installed.
Should I update the year in the footer?
 Yes, please keep the year updated. It should always be the current year. If you are using the
most recent Word templates, the year will update automatically.
Can I use images from the Internet?
 No, all images used in internal emails must be taken from the HPE image library. For
photography style guidelines in general, please refer to the photography standards posted on
HPE Brand Central.
Access photography page
Can I use icons and illustrations?
 Yes, our visual storytelling style is unique and helps make the communication more
attractive. It can be used as a feature artwork or to replace imagery.
Access visual storytelling page

Best practices
Follow these best practices for all types of emails.
Adding text
It’s often easier to add your text to the email, before removing the dummy text on the line.
This better maintains the embedded formatting.
Double check before publishing
Send the email to yourself first, so that you can check the layout on your desktop and mobile
phone before sending.
Size images first
Size the images according to the formatting guidance offered in the Internal Email templates.
Cybersecurity
We all have a responsibility to keep our information secure at HPE. Even internal emails are
susceptible to cyber attacks. Follow these cybersecurity best practices for internal emails.
1. Avoid suspicious content
The following elements can rouse suspicion and should be avoided:
External links.
Executable file attachments, such as .exe or .bat file extensions.
URL shorteners (such as bit.ly or goo.gl).
High-pressure language and formatting (all caps or red text, for example).
2. Provide a verification method
1 3 / 1 3Set up secure email in Outlook and inform your audience to look for your digital signature.
In the message, provide an independent method to validate the email. For example: Contact
our team to verify this email. We are listed as Cyber Security Communications in your
Outlook address book.
3. Practice data security
Requesting sensitive and personal data over email is not a secure practice and creates
suspicion among recipients.

Microsoft Office templates
Overview
To help you create beautiful, on-brand documents, we’ve optimized these Microsoft Office
templates in Word, Excel, Visio, and Power BI. These templates provide you with a starting
point: offering formatting and style guidelines consistent with our Brand Essentials tools for
applying the HPE brand.
Download Word templates
Download Excel template
Download Visio template
Download Power BI template
Word templates
The Word template includes comprehensive instructions for correctly creating commonly
used content (ie: cover page, table of contents, bullets, headers, etc). Correct creation of
content helps ensure brand compliance and accessibility.
The template is available in fonts Arial and MetricHPE on both US Letter and A4 formats.
Once downloaded, open 2 versions of the template: one for referencing all instructions and
one to create your document by deleting everything.
Download Word Templates
Excel template
The Excel template comes with the color palette and MetricHPE automatically set when you
start a worksheet. This set-up makes it easier to create charts and graphics that are on brand
as well as simpler to transfer to other presentations or documents later.
Download Excel Template
Visio template
The Visio template includes the color palette, MetricHPE font and a full set of technical icons
automatically set when you start a worksheet. This set-up makes it easier to create diagrams
and schemes that are on brand.
